    "-Niccolo Machiavelli Two MindsFrom the beginning of the decade of 1930 up to the decade of 1970, surgeons used to cut the connective tissue called the Corpus Callosum (Fig. 2) between the two hemispheres of patients' brains to stop their epilepsy.",
    "What is significant about this brutal and dangerous invasive method, is that patients surprisingly had positive results and were able to live a completely normal life afterwards.",
